.\" ls.types.1 - manpage for ls.types
.\" Generated from ls.types v1.1.0
.TH LS.TYPES 1 "2026-03-23" "ls.types 1.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ls.types \- list script files by shebang or extension using symlink dispatch
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ls.types
.RB [ \-E ]
.RB [ \-S
.IR action ]
.RB [ \-V ]
.RB [ \-h ]
.PP
.I symlink
.RB [ \-d
.IR N ]
.RB [ \-r ]
.RB [ \-l ]
.RB [ \-L ]
.RB [ \-\- ]
.RI [ DIR .\|.\|.]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ls.types
is a single script that serves as multiple commands via symlink dispatch.
Behavior is determined by the invocation name: call it as
.B ls.bash
for Bash files,
.B ls.python
for Python,
.B ls.php
for PHP, and so on.
.PP
Files are matched by shebang line first, falling back to file extension.
Binary files are automatically excluded using
.BR file (1)
MIME encoding detection.
Unreadable files are silently skipped.
.SH OPTIONS
When invoked directly as
.BR ls.types ,
only global options are available.
When invoked via a symlink, all options apply.
.SS Scanning Options
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-maxdepth " " \fIN\fR
Maximum directory depth for
.BR find (1).
Default: 1 (current directory only).
A numeric shorthand
.BI \- N
is also accepted (e.g.,
.B \-3
for depth 3).
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-realpath
Output absolute paths (resolved via
.BR realpath (1)).
Duplicates from multiple directory arguments are removed.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-ls
Format output as an
.B ls \-lhA \-\-color=always \-\-time\-style=long\-iso
listing.
.TP
.BR \-L ", " \-\-follow
Follow symbolic links.
Passes
.B \-L
to both
.BR find (1)
and
.BR file (1),
causing symlinked files and directories to be traversed.
.TP
.B \-\-
End of options.
All subsequent arguments are treated as directories.
.SS Management Options
.TP
.BR \-E ", " \-\-edit
Launch an interactive editor (uses
.BR $EDITOR ,
defaults to
.BR nano )
to modify the configuration file.
Offers to create symlinks after editing.
.TP
.BR "\-S " \fR[\fIACTION\fR]\ [\fIDIR\fR] ", " "\-\-symlinks " \fR[\fIACTION\fR]\ [\fIDIR\fR]
Manage symlinks defined in the configuration file.
.IR ACTION
is one of:
.RS
.TP
.B list
Show all defined symlinks and whether they exist (default).
.TP
.B create
Create missing symlinks in
.I DIR
(defaults to the script directory).
.RE
.SS Informational Options
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print the program name and version number.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display a help summary and exit.
.SS Option Clustering
Short options can be clustered:
.B \-Lrl
is equivalent to
.BR "\-L \-r \-l" .
.SH CONFIGURATION
Type definitions are stored in a colon-delimited configuration file
.BR types.conf .
.SS Format
.PP
.in +4n
.IR symlink : filetype : shebang_pattern : extensions
.in
.TP
.I symlink
Command name and dispatch key (e.g.,
.BR ls.bash ).
.TP
.I filetype
Human-readable label (e.g.,
.BR Bash ).
.TP
.I shebang_pattern
Substring fragment inserted into the regex
.BR ^#!.*\fIpattern\fR .
Must not contain anchors or be a full regex.
.TP
.I extensions
Comma-separated file extensions without dots (e.g.,
.BR sh,bash ).
.SS Example
.PP
.in +4n
.nf
ls.bash:Bash:bash:sh,bash
ls.python:Python:python:py,python
ls.js:JavaScript:node:js,mjs,cjs
ls.sh:Shell:/bin/sh:sh
.fi
.in
.SS Search Order
The first readable configuration file is used (FHS-compliant):
.PP
.in +4n
.nf
/etc/ls.types/types.conf
/usr/local/share/ls.types/types.conf
/usr/share/ls.types/types.conf
\fI<script\-directory>\fR/types.conf
.fi
.in
.SH FILE MATCHING
.PP
For each regular file found by
.BR find (1):
.IP 1. 4
Skip if unreadable or binary (detected via
.BR "file \-\-mime\-encoding" ).
.IP 2. 4
Match the first line against
.BI ^#!.* pattern
(shebang detection).
.IP 3. 4
If no shebang match, check the file extension against the configured extensions.
.IP 4. 4
Files matching either criterion are included in the output.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Configuration not found, invalid directory, unknown symlink, or symlink creation failed.
.TP
.B 22
Invalid option or argument (unknown option, missing or non-numeric
.B \-d
value).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B EDITOR
Editor used by
.BR \-E / \-\-edit .
Defaults to
.BR nano .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/ls.types/types.conf
System-wide type definitions (installed by
.BR "make install" ).
.TP
.I /usr/local/share/ls.types/types.conf
Local override (FHS).
.TP
.I /usr/share/ls.types/types.conf
Distribution-provided definitions.
.SH EXAMPLES
List Bash files in the current directory:
.PP
.in +4n
.B ls.bash
.in
.PP
Search two directories at depth 2 with
.B ls
formatting:
.PP
.in +4n
.B ls.bash \-d 2 \-l /scripts /backup
.in
.PP
List Python files with absolute paths:
.PP
.in +4n
.B ls.python \-r /src
.in
.PP
Follow symlinks and combine with realpath + ls output:
.PP
.in +4n
.B ls.bash \-Lrl /opt/scripts
.in
.PP
Add a new language type:
.PP
.in +4n
.nf
ls.types \-E          # edit config, then create symlinks
ls.ruby .             # use the new type
.fi
.in
.PP
Show available symlinks:
.PP
.in +4n
.B ls.types \-S list
.in
.SH ADDING A NEW TYPE
.IP 1. 4
Edit the configuration file:
.B ls.types \-E
.IP 2. 4
Add a line:
.IR symlink : filetype : pattern : extensions
.IP 3. 4
Create symlinks:
.B ls.types \-S create
.SH SYMLINKS
The following symlinks are provided by default:
.PP
.TS
l l l l.
ls.bash	Bash	bash	sh,bash
ls.python	Python	python	py,python
ls.php	PHP	php	php
ls.js	JavaScript	node	js,mjs,cjs
ls.perl	Perl	perl	pl,pm
ls.ruby	Ruby	ruby	rb
ls.sh	Shell	/bin/sh	sh
.TE
